  "summary_30w": "Former President Trump pleads not guilty to 34 felony counts in a Manhattan court, setting the stage for a high-stakes legal showdown.",
  "article": "Former President Donald Trump has pleaded not guilty to 34 felony counts in a Manhattan court, marking a historic legal battle for the former commander-in-chief. The charges, which include falsifying business records, stem from a hush money payment made to adult film star Stormy Daniels during the 2016 presidential campaign.

The arraignment, which took place on Tuesday, was a highly anticipated event, with Trump becoming the first former U.S. president to face criminal charges. The charges allege that Trump orchestrated a scheme to conceal damaging information about an alleged affair with Daniels in the lead-up to the 2016 election.

